The paper presents an algorithm for submodular optimization over a matroid constraint, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper uses techniques from combinatorial optimization, such as the greedy algorithm and local search, which are commonly studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the runtime of the algorithm, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization of a monotone submodular function, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
